sections.Biography:
===Background===
Wisdom Rossart was a loyal servant of King [[Aerys II Targaryen]], during whose reign the Guild rose again to royal favor. Rossart burned Aerys' enemies alive in the [[Great Hall (Red Keep)|Great Hall]] of the [[Red Keep]]. During the [[War of the Usurper]], he rose to [[Hand of the King]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Alchemists' Guild (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Following the Battle of the Trident, Aerys had Rossart fill King's Landing with secret caches of [[wildfire]] to destroy the city and all those in it should the capital fall to the rebellion. However, Rossart was killed by Ser [[Jaime Lannister]] during the capital's [[Sack of King's Landing|sacking]] to prevent him from carrying out the Mad King's order of destroying the entire city.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Kissed by Fire]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===Season 3===
While feverishly taking a bath in [[Harrenhal]] along [[Brienne of Tarth]], Jaime recalls the turn of events that led him to kill [[Aerys II Targaryen]], indirectly referring to Rossart as &quot;Aerys's pyromancer&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Kissed by Fire]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
